Document: ImporterMeshInstance3D
Path: godot/classes/class_importermeshinstance3d.rst
Summary: Represents a 3D mesh resource imported from an external file, allowing for manipulation and rendering within the scene.

ImporterMeshInstance3D

Inherits: MeshInstance3D < GeometryInstance3D < CullInstance3D < GeometryInstance < Node3D < Node

A 3D node that imports and shows a Mesh resource. This node is used to instance a Mesh resource in the scene.

The Mesh resource must be created by an importer. For example, when importing a glTF scene, the meshes within the glTF scene will be imported as Mesh resources.

This node is a subclass of MeshInstance3D, so it inherits all of its properties and methods.

Properties:
mesh (Mesh): The Mesh resource to be drawn.

Methods:
_get_mesh_list() → Array: Returns a list of available meshes from the importer.
_set_mesh(mesh_index: int) → void: Sets the mesh by its index in the list of available meshes.
get_mesh_list() → Array: Returns a list of available meshes from the importer.
set_mesh(mesh_index: int) → void: Sets the mesh by its index in the list of available meshes.
