Document: ImporterMeshInstance3D
Path: godot/classes/class_importermeshinstance3d.rst
Summary: This section details the properties of the ImporterMeshInstance3D class, including their types, names, and default values.

Properties:
* cast_shadow (ShadowCastingSetting): Controls how the mesh casts shadows. Default: 1.
* layer_mask (int): Determines which physics layers the mesh belongs to. Default: 1.
* mesh (ImporterMesh): The mesh resource to be displayed.
* skeleton_path (NodePath): Path to the Skeleton node that controls the mesh's bones. Default: NodePath("").
* skin (Skin): The skin resource used for skeletal animation.
* visibility_range_begin (float): The near distance at which the mesh starts to fade out. Default: 0.0.
* visibility_range_begin_margin (float): A margin added to the begin distance for fading. Default: 0.0.
* visibility_range_end (float): The far distance at which the mesh completely fades out. Default: 0.0.
* visibility_range_end_margin (float): A margin added to the end distance for fading. Default: 0.0.
* visibility_range_fade_mode (VisibilityRangeFadeMode): The mode used for fading visibility based on distance. Default: 0.
